        "book_cover":"/assets/images/bookpics/thewomaninwhite.jpg",
        "description": "Heroes and heroines are boring and forgettable, villains are much more interesting. Count Fosco in “The Woman in White,” by Wilkie Collins, is a clever villain; evil but likable. (Ayaan as quoted in the New York Times)",
